cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.RO 

The paper proposes a novel approach for single view 3D reconstruction with morphable models, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The use of implicit regularization techniques and optimization methods also suggests a possible connection to machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the application of the proposed method to augmented reality, which is a topic related to robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper provides implementations to facilitate reproducibility and public benchmarking, which is a common practice in the machine learning community (cs.MM).
